# Design System Rules - Indian Coffee Base

## Core Philosophy
**Depth through surfaces, not effects.**
Clean, systematic, coffee-focused design with minimal visual noise.

---

## 1. Surface System (Non-Negotiable)

### Three Surfaces Only
```css
surface-0  → Page background (no shadow)
surface-1  → Cards/panels (shadow-lg, border)
surface-2  → Modals/dropdowns (shadow-xl, border)
```

### Shell Helpers
```css
card-shell  → surface-1 + rounded-lg
modal-shell → surface-2 + rounded-xl
nav-shell   → surface-1 + border-b + shadow-sm
```

**Rule:** Use shells instead of manual utility stacks.

---

## 2. Typography Scale (Locked)

```
.text-hero       → 5xl/6xl/7xl (landing pages only)
.text-display    → 4xl/5xl/6xl (page headers)
.text-title      → 2xl/3xl (section headers)
.text-heading    → xl/2xl (card headers)
.text-subheading → lg/xl (subsections)
.text-body       → base (default)
.text-body-large → lg
.text-body-muted → base + muted color
.text-caption    → sm + muted color
.text-micro      → 12px (minimal background text)
```

**Font families:**
- Display/Title: `font-serif`
- Headings: `font-sans`
- Body: `font-sans` (default)

**Rule:** No custom font sizes. Ever.

---

## 3. Spacing System (Locked)

### Vertical Spacing (Stacks)
```
.stack-xs → gap-2  (8px)
.stack-sm → gap-3  (12px)
.stack-md → gap-6  (24px)
.stack-lg → gap-10 (40px)
```

### Section/Container Spacing
```
.section-spacing   → py-8/12/16 (responsive)
.container-default → max-w-7xl + responsive padding
.card-padding      → p-4/6 (responsive)
```

**Rule:** No arbitrary gaps, padding, or margins. Use defined utilities only.

---

## 4. Shadow System (Simplified)

**Allowed shadows:**
```
shadow-sm  → Nav, subtle elements
shadow-lg  → Cards (surface-1)
shadow-xl  → Modals (surface-2)
```

**Special shadows (rare use):**
```
shadow-premium → Featured cards, hero CTAs
shadow-glow    → Accent elements, hover states
```

**Rule:** Shadows are built into surfaces. Don't add manually.

---

## 5. Radius System

```
rounded-sm   → Small buttons, inputs
rounded-md   → Standard buttons
rounded-lg   → Cards (default)
rounded-xl   → Modals
rounded-full → Badges, pills, avatars
```

**Rule:** No arbitrary radius values like `rounded-[8px]`.

---

## 6. Color System

### Use CSS Variables ONLY
```
--background, --foreground
--card, --card-foreground
--primary, --primary-foreground
--secondary, --secondary-foreground
--muted, --muted-foreground
--accent, --accent-foreground
--border, --input, --ring
```

**Tailwind utilities:**
```
bg-background, bg-card, bg-primary
text-foreground, text-muted-foreground
border-border
```

**Rule:** Never hardcode colors. All colors via CSS variables.

---

## 7. Forbidden Patterns

**NEVER use these:**
```css
❌ backdrop-blur-*        (no blur for depth)
❌ bg-card/80             (no opacity backgrounds for depth)
❌ bg-card/60             (use proper surfaces instead)
❌ shadow-[custom]        (use defined shadows)
❌ text-[20px]            (use typography scale)
❌ gap-[15px]             (use spacing system)
❌ rounded-[12px]         (use radius system)
❌ Arbitrary z-index      (use defined hierarchy)
```

**Allowed - Decorative Gradients:**
```css
✅ bg-gradient-*          (decorative gradients for visual interest)
✅ Gradient text          (bg-gradient-to-r + bg-clip-text)
✅ Gradient buttons/CTAs   (decorative, not for depth)
✅ Gradient backgrounds   (visual interest, not depth)
✅ Image overlays         (bg-gradient-to-t from-black/90 via-black/30)
```

**Rule:** Decorative gradients are fine. Only opacity/blur for DEPTH is forbidden (use surfaces instead).

---

## 8. Component Class Naming

### Conventions
```
Prefix by type:  .card-*, .btn-*, .badge-*
Use kebab-case:  .hero-content, not .heroContent
Be semantic:     .search-input, not .input-lg
```

### Before Creating New Classes
1. Check `src/app/styles/*.css` for existing utilities
2. If used only once → use Tailwind directly
3. If used 2-3+ times → create reusable class in appropriate file

### File Organization
```
globals.css     → Theme, variables, base styles, noise texture
layout.css      → Container, spacing, grid utilities
typography.css  → Text scale, font families
components.css  → Buttons, cards, badges, shells
effects.css     → Animations, transitions, keyframes
```

**Rule:** All custom classes in `@layer components`.

---

## 9. Animation System

### Use Existing Animations
Check `effects.css` for available keyframes:
```
cardFadeIn, fade-in-scale, float, shimmer
slideDown, marquee, marquee-vertical
```

### Animation Delays
```
.delay-0 through .delay-450 (50ms increments)
```

**Rule:** Don't create new animations without checking existing ones first.

---

## 10. Z-Index Hierarchy

**Fixed levels (DO NOT deviate):**
```
z-100  → .header-dropdown (highest)
z-50   → .announcement-bar
z-45   → .mobile-menu
z-40   → .sticky-header
z-0-30 → Regular content, overlays
```

**Rule:** Use defined z-index classes. No arbitrary values.

---

## 11. Responsive Design

### Breakpoints
```
sm:  640px
md:  768px
lg:  1024px
xl:  1280px
2xl: 1400px
```

**Use Tailwind prefixes:**
```
class="text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl"
class="p-4 md:p-6"
```

---

## 12. Dark Mode

**Theme switching:** `.dark` class on parent
**Rule:** All colors auto-adapt via CSS variables. Don't manually create dark variants unless absolutely necessary.

---

## Quick Reference

### Good Patterns ✅
```jsx
<div className="card-shell card-padding">
<h2 className="text-heading">Title</h2>
<div className="stack-sm">
  <p className="text-body">Content</p>
  <p className="text-body-muted">Meta</p>
</div>
</div>
```

### Bad Patterns ❌
```jsx
{/* Using opacity/blur for depth instead of surfaces */}
<div className="bg-card/80 backdrop-blur-md p-[18px] rounded-[14px]">
<h2 className="text-[22px] font-bold">Title</h2>
<div className="flex flex-col gap-[14px]">
  <p className="text-base">Content</p>
</div>
</div>

{/* Decorative gradients are fine! ✅ */}
<div className="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-accent">
  <h2 className="bg-gradient-to-r from-accent to-primary bg-clip-text text-transparent">
    Decorative gradient text
  </h2>
</div>
```

---

## Before Shipping Code

**Checklist:**
- [ ] Using defined surfaces/shells (not manual utility stacks)
- [ ] Using typography scale (no custom sizes)
- [ ] Using spacing system (no arbitrary gaps)
- [ ] Colors via CSS variables only
- [ ] No forbidden patterns (blur, opacity, arbitrary values)
- [ ] Tested in light AND dark mode

---

**Remember:** Constraints breed consistency. When in doubt, use less.
